          "content": "Hello, thank you for sharing your concerns with me. I understand how frightening this situation must be for you. Your symptoms of a severe headache, nausea, and light sensitivity are concerning, especially with the change in your usual migraines. \n\nHowever, based on current guidelines, neuroimaging like a CT scan isn't typically recommended unless there are red flag signs such as sudden severe onset (thunderclap headache), neurological deficits, or if your headache is different from your usual pattern. Since you do not mention any new neurological symptoms or sudden onset, and your exam is normal, it\u2019s likely that this is a severe migraine episode. \n\nThat said, your anxiety and worry are very valid. I strongly recommend you see a healthcare professional promptly for a thorough evaluation and to ensure you receive appropriate care. If your symptoms worsen \u2014 for example, if you develop weakness, vision changes, confusion, or you cannot keep fluids down \u2014 seek emergency care immediately. \n\nRemember, you're not alone, and there are ways to manage this safely. Would you like advice on how to cope with your symptoms or guidance on when to seek urgent care?"
