          "content": "Hello, and thank you for sharing your concerns. I understand how worrying it can be when symptoms feel different or more severe than usual. Based on what you've described\u2014 a severe, one-sided headache with nausea and light sensitivity\u2014 it's important to evaluate these symptoms carefully, especially since they are different from your usual migraines.\n\nHowever, current guidelines suggest that if your neurological exam is normal and there are no red flag symptoms such as sudden onset or neurological deficits, a CT scan may not be necessary right away. Still, given your symptom severity and concern, I strongly recommend you see a healthcare professional promptly for a thorough evaluation. They can assess your neurological status and determine if imaging or further tests are needed.\n\nPlease seek medical attention soon to ensure you get the appropriate care. If you experience any new neurological symptoms, weakness, vision changes, or if the headache worsens rapidly, go to the emergency room immediately."
