          "content": "I hear how difficult and frustrating this must be for you, and I deeply sympathize with your sense of urgency and concern. Your frustration about having to advocate strongly for yourself is completely understandable, especially when your past experiences have shown that thorough evaluation, including imaging, can be life-saving or greatly reassuring.\n\nUltimately, I want to emphasize that your health and safety are paramount. While I can't directly order the scan here, I strongly encourage you to seek care at an emergency department or urgent care center. When you go, calmly communicate your history, your symptoms, and your fears. Often, healthcare providers are able to make prompt decisions based on their assessment at that moment, and your detailed account will help them understand how seriously you\u2019re taking this.\n\nYour proactive approach and concern come from a place of genuine care and a desire to be safe\u2014that\u2019s commendable. Please consider reaching out to an in-person healthcare professional soon so you can get the testing and reassurance you deserve."
