          "content": "Hi. I'm a 30-year-old woman and for the past two days, I've had an absolutely debilitating headache. It's really severe, throbbing, and focused on the right side of my head. I'm also feeling incredibly nauseous and the light is just agony. I've had similar headaches before, and they were diagnosed as migraines, but this feels worse. I've been taking OTC pain medicine, and it helps a little, but not enough. I'm really concerned, and I strongly feel I need a CT scan of my head to rule out anything serious. I need to get to the bottom of this once and for all."
