        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "Hello, thank you for reaching out. I can understand how uncomfortable and anxious you must be. Based on what you've described\u2014symptoms lasting over 8 days, worsening facial pain, pressure, and congestion\u2014it sounds like you may have acute bacterial rhinosinusitis, which can often require antibiotics.\n\nI strongly recommend that you see a healthcare professional as soon as possible for an in-person evaluation. They can assess your symptoms more thoroughly and determine the most appropriate treatment. If it is bacterial sinusitis, antibiotics can help clear the infection and relieve your symptoms. \n\nPlease don\u2019t wait too long, and consider seeking urgent care to ensure you get the right treatment promptly. If your symptoms worsen or you develop new concerns like a high fever, vision changes, or severe headache, go to the emergency room immediately.\n\nYou're not alone, and help is available. Would you like guidance on how to find immediate care nearby?"
