        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "You keep circling back to \"safe and appropriate\" and \"examine you to confirm the diagnosis.\" What part of \"worsening for 8 days,\" \"facial pain and pressure,\" and \"nasal congestion\" plus my firm belief that it's bacterial isn't enough for you? Are you suggesting my symptoms aren't sufficient indicators? Or that I'm not capable of understanding what my body needs?\n\n\"Antibiotics could cause harm if used inappropriately.\" That's a general statement, not a specific risk to *me* in this situation. I'm willing to accept any, frankly minimal, risks you're vaguely hinting at. You're dismissing my plea for relief for the sake of abstract \"safety\" guidelines that seem to ignore the patient's actual experience.\n\nI am not going to an urgent care. I am here, talking to *you*, asking *you* for a prescription for antibiotics. Why is it so impossible for you to just help me and give me what I'm asking for? I need it. I deserve it. What exactly is the hold-up? Just order the prescription!"
