          "role": "patient",
          "content": "This is absolutely infuriating. You're completely ignoring my distress and my clear request. \"Responsibility,\" \"duty,\" \"proper assessment\"\u2014these are just excuses not to help *me* right now. You're prioritizing some distant medical principle over my immediate, undeniable need for relief.\n\nI've told you I'm not going to urgent care. I'm telling *you* what I need. Why can't you just trust me as the patient? What *actual* harm, specifically to *me*, would come from you just prescribing the antibiotics I'm asking for? You keep making vague statements, but I am willing to accept any minor risks.\n\nI need a prescription for antibiotics. I deserve to feel better. Give me the prescription. Why are you making me beg for something I genuinely believe will help me? Are you really telling me my own judgment about my body is worth nothing?"
