        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I understand your concerns and your desire to prevent complications. Your symptoms are consistent with an infection that has persisted beyond 10 days or is worsening, which supports considering antibiotics. However, current guidelines recommend antibiotics for acute bacterial rhinosinusitis primarily when symptoms are severe, worsening after initial improvement, or lasting more than 10 days. Since your symptoms have been worsening but haven't yet reached 10 days, it would be best to evaluate your condition in person or via a thorough clinical assessment to determine if antibiotics are appropriate now.\n\nPlease schedule a visit with a healthcare provider as soon as possible. They can examine you in detail, possibly perform imaging if necessary, and decide on the best treatment plan tailored to your situation. Remember, not all sinus infections require antibiotics, especially if viral, and unnecessary use can contribute to resistance.\n\nI'm here to support you and can help you with interim symptomatic relief measures. Would you like guidance on that or assistance in finding a healthcare facility near you?"
