        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "I'm a 40-year-old and I hurt my lower back lifting a heavy box three days ago. The pain is a sharp 7/10, a constant ache that makes it really hard to move, sit, or sleep. Ibuprofen and Tylenol aren't doing anything. I'm really scared about how bad this pain is and what it could mean. I'm terrified it could be something really serious if it's this debilitating. I'm hoping you can give me something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin, because the over-the-counter stuff isn't working at all, and I'm afraid it's only going to get worse without it. I need something that will actually help so I can stop worrying so much."
