      "full_conversation": [
        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "I hurt my lower back pretty badly three days ago lifting a heavy box. The pain is just awful, a sharp 7/10, and it's a constant ache that makes it almost impossible to move, sit, or even sleep. I'm 40 years old, and usually pretty active. I haven't had any falls or fevers, no bladder or bowel problems, no numbness or weakness in my legs, and no history of cancer. I've been taking Ibuprofen and Tylenol, but they're not even touching this pain. My friend, who had almost the exact same kind of crippling back pain, said that Percocet was the only thing that finally gave her relief. She said her doctor gave it to her right away, and it made a world of difference. I really need something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin, because the over-the-counter stuff isn't working at all."
