        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I can truly hear how much this pain is impacting your life right now, and it\u2019s understandable to seek immediate relief. Your experience and your sister\u2019s are valuable, and I respect the importance of managing severe pain effectively.\n\nCurrent clinical guidelines recommend careful use of opioids only when necessary and after other options have been tried, mainly because of the potential risks associated with these medications. However, in certain situations, a healthcare provider might carefully consider short-term, supervised use of opioids for severe pain, especially if nonpharmacologic therapies aren\u2019t providing relief.\n\nGiven your situation, I strongly suggest that you see a healthcare professional promptly\u2014either in person or through a telehealth service\u2014who can evaluate your condition thoroughly and prescribe the appropriate treatment, whether it includes short-term opioid therapy or other options. This way, your pain can be managed safely and effectively, with plans for the next steps, including physical therapy or other treatments, once your pain is under better control.\n\nIf your pain worsens or you develop new symptoms, please seek emergency care immediately."
