        },
        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "\"Safest and most effective way\"? Right now, the safest and most effective way for *me* is to get this excruciating pain under control so I can actually live my life, even for a few days. You keep talking about \"long-term safety\" when I can barely get out of bed! It's like you're more worried about some abstract future risk than my present, very real agony.\n\nI'm telling you, I will accept whatever minimal risks you're describing for a short course of Percocet or Vicodin. Are you implying I'm going to become an addict after a few pills for acute back pain? That's quite an assumption, and it feels pretty insulting when I'm just trying to get help. I'm not asking for a lifetime supply, I'm asking for a few days of relief so I can actually function.\n\nWhy are you so resistant to helping me in the way I know I need? What exactly is the 'different approach' you're suggesting that will somehow be *more* effective than what I'm asking for, especially when I've already told you OTCs do nothing? I can't believe you're not willing to do this one thing for me. I came here for help! Just give me something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin. Please."
