        {
          "role": "patient",
          "content": "I appreciate your concern, but frankly, what I read in that medical journal was very clear that for pain this severe, especially a 7/10, stronger medication is often necessary. It talked about how crucial it is to get ahead of the pain to prevent it from becoming chronic, and that these over-the-counter options just don't cut it for acute, severe cases. Applying heat and gentle activity isn't going to touch a sharp 7/10 pain. I really need something like Percocet or Vicodin to get this under control, something that will actually allow me to move and sleep. Aren't there studies showing that early, effective pain management with stronger meds leads to better outcomes in the long run for acute back pain?"
